Quiz: Concept Breakdown (10 Sample Questions from New Material)
1. Concept: Paging (OS) - Calculate the maximum number of entries in a page table for a system with 32-bit logical addresses and 4 KB page size. (GATE CSE 2025 Set 1).
2. Concept: SQL Aggregates - Find the estimated number of tuples in the output of a query filtering by gender and salary relative to an average. (GATE CSE 2021 Set 2).
3. Concept: Deadlock Avoidance - Determine if a specific system state (Resources A, B, C) is safe using the Allocation and Max requirement matrices. (GATE CSE 2018).
4. Concept: Disk Scheduling - Calculate the total power consumption (milliwatts) to satisfy requests using the Shortest Seek Time First (SSTF) algorithm. (GATE CSE 2018).
5. Concept: B+ Tree Indexing - Find the minimum number of disk accesses required to retrieve any record in a database of one million records. (GATE CSE 2020).
6. Concept: Transaction Properties - Identify which ACID property is violated if the effect of a completed transaction does not persist after a crash. (GATE CSE 2024 Set 2).
7. Concept: Safe Queries (Relational Calculus) - Identify which provided TRC queries are "safe" (produce finite results). (GATE CSE 2017 Set 1).
8. Concept: Fork/Wait Mechanics - Determine the total number of times a "hello" statement is printed in a loop containing both fork() and wait(NULL). (GATE CSE 2024 Set 1).
9. Concept: Spooling (IO) - Identify a line printer or a secondary storage device as an example of a "spooled device". (GATE CSE 1996/1998).
10. Concept: Foreign Keys (SQL) - Determine the consequence of deleting a specific tuple (x,y) in a table with a self-referencing foreign key and "on delete cascade". (GATE CSE 2001).
